Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet} and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized pieces.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board. Cut into 2cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

While the chorizo cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{24%grams}, @honey{15%grams}, chorizo (including the oil from the pan) and the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for amount). Season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{}, then mix in the tomato chunks.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once the chorizo is cooked, allow to cool for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add to your #bowl{} of tomatoes (including the oil from the pan).

Once the potatoes are cooked, remove them from the oven and scoop into a large bowl. Allow to cool slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooled, add the baby gem, avocado chunks and mint to the bowl. Pour over the chorizo, tomatoes and the dressing from the bowl. Season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{}. Mix to combine.

Divide the summer salad between your #bowls{}.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{30%grams} to finish. Enjoy!